privy - sharing in the knowledge of (something secret or private). (aware of)

feigned - simulated or pretended; insincere.

hostile - showing or feeling opposition or dislike; unfriendly. (aggressive)

levity - the treatment of a serious matter with humour or lack of due respect.

quivering -  to shake or move with a slight trembling motion.

scorn - a feeling and expression of contempt or disdain for someone or something.

contempt - the feeling that a person or a thing is worthless or beneath consideration.

abortive sorrows - "Abortive" means "failing to produce results," so it denotes a sorrow, probably short-lived, that doesn't cause the person to change.
